data.name: label2.Text
data.value: Each player will begin with 3 chips. During the player's turn, if they have 3 or less chips, they will roll that amount of dice. If the player has more than they, they will only roll 3 dice and will keep the extra chips. If they roll (L) then a chip goes to the player to the left. if (R) then a chip goes to the player to the right. If (C) they keep the chip. If (Cirlce) then the chip is out of the game entirely. The game keeps going until their is only one chip left. If the person with the last chip rolls a (C) then they win or a (Circle) then they roll again.

data.name: RulesTextBox.Text
data.value: Each player will start off with 3 chips. Going counter-clockwise each player will roll the amount of dice for every chip they have unless it is more than 3. If the player has more than 3 chips they will roll 3 dice and keep the additional chips for that round. If the player rolls (L) then a chip goes to the player to the left. . If (C) then the player keeps the chip. If (R) then a chip goes the player to the right. if (Circle) then the chip is out the game for good. You are not out the game if you have no chips as the players next to you might have to pass one to you! Eventually, when it comes down to 1 chip left, whoever has the chip and rolls (C) wins the game! If you roll (Circle) then that player rolls again. Enjoy!
